cs351.core.Engine

Interface EvolutionEngine

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Engine

    public interface EvolutionEngine
    An evolution engine sets the stage for the entire process of the mutation/evolution of a population. As part of its initialization, it should take the file path to a target image which it will load and translate the image data into a target genome. It should also drive the seeding of the initial population and initialization of any other critical systems to be used during the process. An external source should be responsible for calling its nextGeneration() function, which should perform all necessary steps to move from the current generation to the next and then signal the GUI when it is a good and thread-safe time to update.

      • init

        void init(java.lang.String[] cmdArgs,
          javafx.stage.Stage stage,
          Population population,
          GUI mainGUI)
        NOTE :: If the population is set to null, the engine will run in a very limited state. If mainGUI is set to null, the engine will run and output its current status to the console each generation. Initializes the engine with the given image file (also calls the renderer's init function at a good point during the engine's init sequence).
        Parameters:
        cmdArgs - (OPTIONAL) list of command line arguments for the engine to use, but this should be completely optional - just don't pass it a null value (pass in a length 0 String array)
        stage - stage object so the engine can initialize the main GUI
        population - population to use to run the simulation
        mainGUI - gui to use

      • beginShutdown

        void beginShutdown()
        Tells the engine that it needs to begin shutting down. Things that might prevent immediate shutdown include the engine waiting on existing jobs to terminate. Once this is called and everything the engine is waiting on has finished, it will shut down all subsystems it manages and terminate.
